ABI Management and C++ Symbols
------------------------------

This package intentionally utilizes a versioned 'shlibs' control file
(debian/libwk2gtkpdf0.shlibs) rather than a '.symbols' file for
ABI dependency tracking.

As noted in the Debian Wiki and Maintainer guidance:
"For C++ libraries it is often better not to ship symbols files."

The decision to revert to shlibs was driven by:
 1. C++ Template Volatility: The extensive use of std::regex and
    Standard Library templates results in a high volume of ephemeral
    mangled symbols (e.g., _ZGVZNKSt8__detail...) that vary between
    compiler versions and optimization levels.
 2. Toolchain Regression: During the Sid (Unstable) 2026 build cycle,
    the 'Build-Depends-Package' metadata field in the symbols parser
    consistently triggered uninitialized hash errors in
    Dpkg::Shlibs::SymbolFile.pm (line 267).

Maintenance Note:
The 'symbols' approach should be periodically re-tested against
future iterations of the dpkg-dev toolchain to determine if
upstream has resolved these parser regressions and if a
manageable regex-based symbol filter can be implemented
without excessive maintenance overhead.


Headless Rendering & Xvfb Orchestration
---------------------------------------
The rendering engine utilizes a systemd-managed Xvfb instance (xvfb.service)
via sd-bus. To ensure secure, unprivileged execution in server-side
environments, a custom Polkit rule (50-wk2gtkpdf.rules) is included.
This allows the 'libwk2gtkpdf0' library to manage the lifecycle of the
display server without requiring root escalation or a persistent
user session.

PoDoFo 0.9.x Compatibility
--------------------------
The library is architected for PoDoFo 0.9.8, which is the current
stable target in Debian Sid and Trixie. This ensures immediate
usability without requiring experimental backports of the
breaking 0.10.x branch.

The library includes conditional compilation logic (-DPODOFO_010) to
bridge the API divergence between PoDoFo 0.9.x and 0.10.x This
ensures ABI stability and eases the path for future development and
enables support for distributions whose default is 0.10.x.

WebKit2GTK Process Lifecycle
----------------------------
To prevent 'zombie' WebProcess or NetworkProcess orphans common in
multiplexed WebKit environments, the library implements RAII-based
process management. The previous use of exit() calls has been
refactored to standard C++ exceptions (std::runtime_error) to allow
calling applications to handle fatal rendering errors without
uncontrolled process termination.
